                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1233.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-19T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your February 18, 10 p.m. Insular Bureau will call Vick’s attention to previous
                    orders to grant five thousand a day. Department assumes this will insure advance
                    of this amount temporarily.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
